  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "ELECTRICAL SUPERVISOR",
  "description": "<p>Job Description & Requirements</p><p>Roles & Responsibilities</p><p>Responsible for supervising daily site operations, ensuring safety compliance, coordinating workers and subcontractors, and supporting the Project Manager to deliver the project on time and within quality standards.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Supervise and monitor daily construction activities on site. Supervise electrical installation works (LV/MV systems, lighting, power, earthing, lightning protection)</p></li><li><p>Coordinate manpower, materials, and subcontractors to ensure smooth workflow.</p></li><li><p>Ensure all works follow safety regulations, method statements, and company procedures.</p></li><li><p>Conduct site inspections and report progress or issues to the Project Manager.</p></li><li><p>Check workmanship quality and ensure compliance with drawings and specifications.</p></li><li><p>Assist in resolving site problems and provide timely solutions.</p></li><li><p>Prepare daily site reports, attendance, and basic documentation.</p></li><li><p>Support safety officers in maintaining a safe working environment.</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Relevant experience in construction site supervision.</p></li><li><p>Able to read basic construction drawings.</p></li><li><p>Strong coordination and communication skills.</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of WSH (Workplace Safety & Health) rules in Singapore is an advantage.</p></li><li><p>Able to work independently and handle site challenges.</p></li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 4,
